    "<p>Historian of ancient Greek and Roman sculpture; professor at the University in Strasbourg, 1872-1910.": [],
    "Michaelis' uncle was the classical art historian <a href=\"/jahno\">Otto Jahn</a>, who first interested him in ancient studies.": [],
    "Michaelis began classical studies in philology and archaeology from in 1853 at the university in Leipzig.": [],
    "In addition to his uncle, he also attended classes in Leipzig under <a href=\"/overbeckj\">Johannes Overbeck</a>.": [],
    "He traveled to Berlin where he further studied with Gerhard B\u00f6ckh (1785-1867) and <a href=\"/curtiuse\">Ernst Curtius</a>.": [
        [
